  "text": "As mTORC2 can phosphorylate Akt during translation and given that mTORC1 function involves translation initiation, we questioned whether mTORC2 also has a role in translation. By metabolic labelling of newly synthesized proteins, we found that although there was no difference at early time points as previously reported [CITATION_1] ), a marked decrease in translation occurred by 60 min in serum-restimulated SIN1 À/À cells in comparison with wild type ( Figure 4A ). Re-expression of SIN1b in SIN1 À/À cells restored translation levels, confirming that the defect is due to the absence of SIN1. Treatment of cells using Torin1 further diminished translation at longer time point (60 min) in both wild-type and SIN1 À/À MEFs, suggesting that both mTORC1",
